<li><strong>Humidification:</strong> A humidifier can be used to put moisture in the room, and that is helpful in easing respiratory problems, throat irritation, and coughing.</li>



<li><strong>Avoid Smoking and Secondhand Smoke: </strong>Tobacco smoke is likely to trigger respiratory problems and make them worse. Do not expose yourself to any kind of smoke in order to prevent other issues from developing.</li>



<li><strong>Practice Good Hygiene:</strong> Take showers frequently; use alcoholic base on hand sanitizers; and avoid people-to-people contact to check the spread of the virus.</li>



<li><strong>Breathing Exercises:</strong> Several preventive measures for Shortness of breath you should try include Gentle, deep breathing exercises that enable the lungs to be expanded. Breathing techniques such as diaphragmatic breathing can, therefore, be quite useful.</li>



<li><strong>Avoid Stress:</strong> Stress that is prolonged is known for breaking the body’s immunity, meaning taking longer to heal. It is suggested that one take up hobbies such as meditation, yoga, and deep breathing exercises in order to counter the ill effects of stress.</li>



<li><strong>Limit Physical Activity:</strong> Moderate physical activity is allowed so that strong exercise or physical exertion that can cause strains on the body while recovering from HMPV should not be encouraged.</li>
</ul>



