<li><strong><a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://weclinic.in/blog/lycopodium-clavatum-uses" title="Lycopodium Clavatum" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked" data-wpil-monitor-id="2456">Lycopodium Clavatum</a></strong>: It lowers appetite when accompanied by conditions such as bloat, digestive discomfort, or gas.</li>



<li><strong><a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://weclinic.in/blog/antimonium-crudum-uses" title="Antimonium Crudum" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked" data-wpil-monitor-id="2461">Antimonium Crudum</a></strong>: It is used for loss of appetite in children or adults due to overeating or indigestion.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Homeopathic Treatment for Loss of Appetite in Children</h3>



<p>Lack of appetite in children can be occasioned by factors such as teething, infection as well as some changes in their emotional well-being. Homeopathy provides mild products that can create an urge for food in them without facet effects.</p>



