<li><strong><a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://weclinic.in/blog/chamomilla-homeopathic-uses" title="Chamomilla" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked" data-wpil-monitor-id="2459">Chamomilla</a></strong>: For irritable children who refuse food, particularly during teething or when they are restless.</li>



<li><strong><a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://weclinic.in/blog/cina-homeopathic-uses" title="Cina" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked" data-wpil-monitor-id="2450">Cina</a> Maritima</strong>: Effective for children with appetite loss caused by intestinal worms, accompanied by irritability and abdominal discomfort.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Homeopathic Treatment for Loss of Appetite in Adults</h3>



<p>In adults, appetite loss may be secondary to stress or other medical illnesses, use of certain medications, or emotional issues. These changes actually reduce appetite, and homeopathic remedies can affect repair work to correct them. Due to this understanding of the particularity of causes and symptoms of appetite loss, homeopathy can provide personalized and effective means for both children and adults.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Nux Vomica</strong>: Primely useful when one is acting on nervousness, gluttony, or a typical sedentary life pattern.</li>



