<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Dosage of Homeopathic Medicine for Loss of Appetite</h3>



<p>The dosage of homeopathic medicine for loss of appetite varies based on several factors, including the individual&#8217;s age, the severity of their symptoms, the underlying cause, and their overall health. Homeopathic remedies are available in different potencies (such as 6X, 30C, and 200C) and forms, including tablets, pellets, or liquid dilutions.</p>



<p>For moderate symptoms, it is generally recommended to take 2–3 pellets or 5 drops in water, 2–3 times a day until symptoms improve or the underlying cause of appetite loss is identified. Continue this regimen for 3–5 days and reassess your progress.</p>



<p>It&#8217;s important to take the medicine on an empty stomach or at least 30 minutes before or after eating or drinking (except for water). Avoid touching the pellets with your hands; instead, use the cap or a spoon to place them under your tongue.</p>



