										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p class="has-luminous-vivid-amber-background-color has-background"><strong>Summary:</strong> Homeopathic Treatment for Cold offers a natural approach to managing symptoms like runny nose, sneezing, and congestion. Remedies such as Arsenic Album, Aconite, and Allium Cepa help alleviate discomfort and boost the body&#8217;s self-healing mechanism.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">What is Cold?</h2>



<p>A cold, or the common Cold, is an easily acquired mild illness, which is viral, more often rhinovirus. It especially impacts the nasal passages, throat, and nasal sinuses. The main signs are a cold, <a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://weclinic.in/blog/how-homeopathy-can-help-in-treating-cough" title="cough" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked" data-wpil-monitor-id="2339">cough</a>, runny nose, sometimes sneezing, sore throat, cough, and sometimes slight fever. You may also be tired or have mild joint pains. Flu is also contagious since it moves in the air in small particles every time an infected individual breathes, coughs, sneezes, or comes into contact with affected objects.</p>



<p>They normally take 7- 10 days, but in some instances, you could continue experiencing symptoms for a more extended period. For this condition, the treatment entails taking a lot of water and other fluids, avoiding handling shoes, and using other treatments such as steam or honey in case of discomfort. Antibiotics will not help to treat colds because colds result from viral infections and not from bacteria. Suggestions such as washing hands frequently reduce the chances of getting a cold.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Symptoms of Cold</h2>



<p>The symptoms can vary depending on the underlying cause, but common signs include</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Runny or Stuffy Nose:</strong> A runny nose occurs when there is an excess of mucus required to tame it or congestion in the nasal passage.</li>



<li><strong><a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://weclinic.in/blog/how-to-treat-sore-throat-with-homeopathy" title="Sore Throat" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked" data-wpil-monitor-id="2341">Sore Throat</a></strong>: Throat inflammation or scratchiness, also called sore throat.</li>



<li><strong>Cough</strong>: Can be dry or with mucus.</li>



